          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The positrons were recorded with a tube electrometer,",
                "assembled with an EM-3 electronic tube, which was",
                "placed in a vacuum.",
                "The basic parts of the apparatus are the following:",
                "a) Faraday cylinder, which was used in a dual",
                "capacity: first, to measure the current passing",
                "through it to make sure it was not entering through",
                "the side walls of the cylinder; secondly, to permit",
                "the introduction through lead of a retarding",
                "potential for stopping the electrons knocked out of",
                "the target by the beam; b) collecting electrode",
                " (collector), which was used to collect the positrons",
                "emitted by the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
